rComments: He is a great professor keeping the class engaged and you actually learn something. He uses a random name generator to call on students but as long as you try he is happy. I wouldn't even buy the book because I looked at it once. He has an extra credit assignment that is a lot of work, but it is worth it because it can boost your grade up to 5%.

Aronoff rocks. I thought neuroscience would be an awful class but his lectures are so interesting. He truly cares about his students wants them to do well. He offers a 5% extra credit research paper.. so there is really no excuse not to do well in this class.

The lectures use a name picking software that calls you out in class, but it is very helpful and makes you pay attention more. He's really good at given lectures and makes the content interesting. I really like this class.
